 A truck carrying a load of wood lost control and came to rest within the marshes around 03:00. A passing motorist who stopped to look at the accident was then rear ended and the vehicle flipped at around 07:00.
Traffic came to a standstill as a recovery of the vehicles is taking place.  Because of the truck’s location, the lanes will have to be closed for retrieval and N4 TRAC teams are planning a detour to ease traffic. It is unknown at this point when the road will be open for use again.      Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za